WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.020
Okay, so I was tasked to present the updated in-mind analysis, and this is a study of

00:00:09.020 --> 00:00:13.560
tafacitimab, lenalidomide, and rituximab in relapsed refractory follicular lymphoma.

00:00:14.020 --> 00:00:20.460
We will be doing a focused analysis looking at the clinical characteristics and outcomes by age.

00:00:23.240 --> 00:00:28.100
So the incidence of follicular lymphoma increases with age, as we all know,

00:00:28.100 --> 00:00:32.900
and most patients will eventually develop relapsed refractory disease requiring

00:00:32.900 --> 00:00:40.100
sequential therapies. Tafacitimab is a humanized monoclonal antibody CD19-directed,

00:00:40.140 --> 00:00:44.120
and it is approved in combination with lenalidomide and rituximab for relapsed

00:00:44.120 --> 00:00:50.820
refractory follicular lymphoma. In the primary analysis of in-mind, tafa with R-squared

00:00:50.820 --> 00:00:56.200
demonstrated a significant improvement in PFS compared to placebo with R-squared,

00:00:56.200 --> 00:00:57.920
and this was associated with a 50%.

00:00:58.100 --> 00:01:04.860
In the secondary analysis of in-mind, tafacitimab showed a 27% reduction in the risk of progression

00:01:04.860 --> 00:01:11.320
or death. The safety profile in in-mind essentially showed that the addition of

00:01:11.320 --> 00:01:16.040
tafacitimab was consistent with the known toxicities of R-squared-based therapy.

00:01:18.800 --> 00:01:26.220
So the objective of this study was to perform a post hoc analysis of efficacy and safety in patients

00:01:26.220 --> 00:01:28.020
with FL who were treated in the in-mind trial,

00:01:28.020 --> 00:01:30.640
and to find out if they had been treated in the in-mind trial or not.

00:01:30.640 --> 00:01:36.260
So just a quick reminder, in-mind was a Phase III double-blind randomized placebo-controlled

00:01:36.260 --> 00:01:43.800
international multi-center trial. Eligible patients were 18 years and older. They had to

00:01:43.800 --> 00:01:49.980
have relapsed refractory CD19-positive and CD20-positive follicular lymphoma, grades 1 to 3A,

00:01:50.320 --> 00:01:56.120
and they also needed to have at least one prior systemic therapy, including an anti-CD20 monoclonal

00:01:56.120 --> 00:01:58.000
antibody. Patients who were treated in the in-mind trial were 18 years and older. They had to have

00:01:58.000 --> 00:01:58.420
relapsed refractory CD20-positive and CD20-positive follicular lymphoma, grades 1 to 3A, and they also

00:01:58.420 --> 00:01:58.920
needed to have at least one prior systemic therapy, including an anti-CD20 monoclonal antibody.

00:01:58.920 --> 00:02:01.040
Patients were randomized in a one-to-one ratio to receive either

00:02:01.040 --> 00:02:06.880
tafacitimab or placebo with R-squared for up to 12, 28-day cycles.

00:02:07.760 --> 00:02:12.800
Patients who had moderate renal insufficiency, and this was defined as a creatinine clearance

00:02:12.800 --> 00:02:19.600
of 30 to less than 60, were also eligible to participate in this study. And for those patients,

00:02:19.600 --> 00:02:24.080
the starting lenalidomide dose was reduced at 10 milligrams daily.

00:02:26.880 --> 00:02:27.920
So the clinic

00:02:27.920 --> 00:02:34.080
clinical characteristics and outcomes were analyzed by predefined age subgroups,

00:02:34.080 --> 00:02:40.720
less than 65 versus 65 years and older, less than 75 versus 75 years and older,

00:02:40.720 --> 00:02:45.200
and 65 and older versus less than 75 years.

00:02:45.200 --> 00:02:51.760
Efficacy endpoints included PFS and time to next treatment, and the safety assessments included

00:02:51.760 --> 00:02:57.840
the incidence and severity of treatment emergent AEs, and that included any events that led to

00:02:57.840 --> 00:03:01.680
discontinuation, dose delays or interruptions, or dose reductions.

00:03:04.160 --> 00:03:11.520
So here we see the baseline characteristics. Overall, 548 FL patients participated in InMind,

00:03:11.520 --> 00:03:18.160
273 received the TAPA-containing arm, and 275 received the placebo-containing arm.

00:03:18.800 --> 00:03:24.080
Across both treatment arms, 50% of the patients were 65 years and older,

00:03:24.720 --> 00:03:31.760
and 20% were 75 years and older. In the 75 years and older age subgroup,

00:03:32.640 --> 00:03:37.600
those patients had a higher proportion of ECOG performance status of 1 to 2,

00:03:37.600 --> 00:03:42.000
moderate renal insufficiency, and a LPI score of 3 or higher.

00:03:45.040 --> 00:03:50.800
So the mean relative dose intensity of tafacitimab was similar across all age subgroups.

00:03:50.800 --> 00:03:57.040
Lenalidomide exposure was decreased in patients who were 75 years and older,

00:03:57.680 --> 00:04:02.960
but it was still generally comparable across creatinine clearance subgroups within each age

00:04:02.960 --> 00:04:12.720
category. In respects to efficacy, we do see an improved PFS and time to next treatment with

00:04:12.720 --> 00:04:13.360
tafacitimab in patients less than 65 years and older. In the 75 years and older age subgroups,

00:04:13.360 --> 00:04:13.360
the mean relative dose intensity of tafacitimab was similar across all age subgroups. Lenalidomide exposure was

00:04:13.360 --> 00:04:15.360
decreased in patients who were 65 years and older. In respects to efficacy, we do see an improved

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:17.680
PFS and time to next treatment with tafacitimab in patients less than 65 years and older.

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:25.520
Improved median PFS with tafacitimab was also observed across all age subgroups.

00:04:27.920 --> 00:04:31.120
And here we see the safety outcomes by age subgroup.

00:04:31.840 --> 00:04:36.560
The observed toxicities were consistent with the known safety profile of these agents

00:04:36.560 --> 00:04:40.880
across all subgroups. There were no new safety signals identified in any subgroup.

00:04:42.320 --> 00:04:43.280
So to conclude, in the 70 years and older age subgroup, the mean relative dose intensity of

00:04:43.280 --> 00:04:46.000
tafacitimab was reduced. In this post hoc analysis of the InMind trial,

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:51.280
TAFA with R-squared reduced the risk of progression or death irrespective of age,

00:04:51.280 --> 00:04:55.840
including patients up to 88 years and even those with moderate renal impairment.

00:04:56.640 --> 00:05:00.560
The safety profile was manageable and consistent across age subgroups. There

00:05:00.560 --> 00:05:08.000
were no new safety signals identified. So to summarize, TAFA R-squared represents a

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:13.200
standard of care option for relapsed refractory FL. It demonstrates consistent efficacy and tolerability.

00:05:13.200 --> 00:05:22.640
So I'd like to thank the patients, the family, the investigators who participated in InMind,

00:05:22.640 --> 00:05:27.520
this was clearly a global effort. Thank you.
